
kernel parameters

	format: -<option> <value>

	-vocality <value>:		: printing information during startup
		
		values:
		stfu			disables initial output, only critical errors are reported
		quiet-please		reports errors and warnings
		normal			reports errors, warnings and important initial information
		vocal			reports all importand information
		report-everything	reports everything happening during initialization

	-force <option> <value>		: forces option to value
		options:
			kb-scan-code-set <value>
					forces keyboard scan code set to X
					keyboard driver will not ask keyboard to change scan code set
					may be useful with emulator virtual keyboard issues
			kb-scan-code-set-noask <value>
					assumes that set X is used and does not ask for it
